✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: I accept this contribution.
This clash challenges string management, translation, dictionaries, and managing impossible scenarios. I had a fun time with it.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: fun fact: they're actually called strobogrammatic numbers, and there is actually a puzzle about if if you're interested:
https://www.codingame.com/training/hard/strobogrammatic-numbers

otherwise, nice problem for clash

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Cool CoC entry; not too hard, yet interesting.

Goal
* Please remove the two line breaks within paragraph 2.

Input
* Next N lines: Please add "[[number]]" in the description (to define the variable for reuse in Constraints section, see next two points after next).

Output
* Please format "[[N]] lines" in <<bold>>.

Constraints
* Please change "[[digit string length]]" to "length of [[number]]".

* Please change "All input numbers are" to "[[number]] is".

* Please delete ", etc."

Cases
* Validator 2: Please include 0 as one of the input numbers.

* (If any of the comments below result in too few hints for Reverse mode, you may consider shifting some input numbers to earlier cases.)

* More Variation (test 5): Please increase the lengths of the input numbers to 10 to 40.

* Validator 5: Same comment as test 5.

* Spin Spin Spin (test 6): Please increase the lengths of the input numbers to 40 to 70, some of them with the output "Impossible".

* Validator 6: Same comment as test 6.

* Long Number (test 7): Please add input numbers with the output "Impossible".

* Validator 7: Same comment as test 7.

Thanks.
Now that is cool, thanks for sharing!
